      h2(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/popover-dynamic.html") Dynamic Popover
      p Framework7 allows you to create Popover dynamically by passing its HTML to related App methods:
      p
        span.method myApp.popover(<span>popoverHTML</span>, <span>target</span>, <span>removeOnClose</span>)</span> - open Popover with <strong>popoverHTML</strong> content around <strong>target</strong> element
      ul.method-parameters
        li
          span.parameter popoverHTML
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">string</span>. HTML string of popover 
        li
          span.parameter target
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">HTMLElement</span> or <span class="parameter-type">string</span> (with CSS Selector) of target element to set popover position around this element. Requred
        li
          span.parameter removeOnClose
          |  - <span class="parameter-type">boolean</span>. Optional, by default - true. If true then Popover will be removed from DOM when closed
        li.method-returns This method returns dynamically created Popover's HTMLElement
      pre
        code
          | &lt;body&gt;
          |   ...
          |   &lt;div class="navbar"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="navbar-inner"&gt;
          |       &lt;div class="left"&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="link create-about"&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          |       &lt;div class="center"&gt;Popover&lt;/div&gt;
